originalText.text: This parking facility damaged my vehicle and then gave me a report. Told me wait and I would be reached. There has been ZERO response back on what the next steps are in fixing my vehicle. I have been reaching out over a month. If anyone is having the same issue please comment as well. I would like to know if your accident was taken care. This is so beyond unprofessional!

originalText.text:
I LOVED my experience with this company. I was staying in the city for two days and was not sure where I was supposed to park. You just pull into the lot up to where it says stop and then tell them how long you will need to leave your car. You do not have to pay anything when you drop it off. You pay when you pick it up. I downloaded their app (MPG Manhatten Parking) which you can also use to make reservations throughout the city at their other lots too.
I downloaded the app right on the spot and paid for the first two nights. I extended my trip to a third day and just showed up when I was ready to collect my car and paid the balance due. You pay by the amount of minutes your car is there.
Daily reservations do not allow for you to take your car in and out. So take everything you need with you.
It is open 24/7. They have security guards as well.
It is on the corner of 34th street and 9th avenue, also on the right side of 9th avenue, with two entrances.
